item.title: Austin City Limits Celebrates 40 Years "Not Fade Away"
item.description:
Austin City Limits Celebrates 40 Years "Not Fade Away"

An all-star lineup celebrating four decades of Austin City Limits culminates in Buddy Holly's classic "Not Fade Away." Watch the special on Friday, October 3rd on PBS at 9E/8C.

item.title: Start Fresh: Never Give Up
item.description:
Start Fresh: Never Give Up

Austin, TX, USA -- Selected works from the HOPE Outdoor Gallery presented using hyperlapse and motion timelapse photographic techniques. All works were painted and filmed in the summer and fall of 2013 using only manual camera movements (i.e. no motion control hardware, sliders, or dollies).

item.title: Old School Austin Groove
item.description:
Old School Austin Groove

This groovin' track is a collaboration between cosmic rockers Shawn Sahm (son of Sir Doug) and Kevin Russell (Shinyribs). It was written and recorded for the documentary Crazy Carl and His Man-Boobs: An Austin Love Story. The movie is online for free at http://beefandpie.com/crazy-carl.

item.title: Spectral Austin
item.description:
Spectral Austin

Three summer days and three summer nights in Austin. "Spectral Austin" was shot in the summer of 2013 as my second solo timelapse and hyperlapse project. My goal was to present the city by both day and night, showing the perpetual beauty of our bustling hill country capital during my favorite season of the year.

item.title: Riding the Light
item.description:
Riding the Light

Take a soaring journey across Austin, the Live Music Capital of the World. Shot in the winter of 2014-2013, "Riding the Light" presents the Austin skyline as you've never seen it before. I'm excited and proud to share this short film, my third solo hyperlapse cityscape project.
